WEBVTT

00:00.492 --> 00:04.562
♪♪

00:10.933 --> 00:12.199
Wow.

00:12.258 --> 00:13.960
Yeah.

00:16.952 --> 00:18.351
What time is it?

00:18.425 --> 00:20.062
I don't know.

00:20.087 --> 00:21.954
What day is it?

00:22.283 --> 00:23.850
Uh, Tuesday?

00:23.875 --> 00:25.781
[Chuckles]

00:25.906 --> 00:27.192
Oh, no, it's Wednesday.

00:27.227 --> 00:28.797
[Sighs]

00:28.822 --> 00:29.994
I have a shift tonight.

00:30.030 --> 00:31.296
Yeah, me, too.

00:31.341 --> 00:33.540
[Chuckles]

00:33.940 --> 00:36.579
So, um...

00:37.130 --> 00:41.459
you know that this was just...
This just happened, right?

00:41.484 --> 00:43.021
Oh, yeah. Don't worry.

00:43.046 --> 00:45.919
No, I... I can separate work and...
and this.

00:45.955 --> 00:47.623
- Mmm. Well, that's good.
- Yeah.

00:47.648 --> 00:49.929
I think we broke at least
a hundred H.R. rules.

00:49.954 --> 00:51.488
We? Oh, no, no, no.

00:51.519 --> 00:54.020
I'm, um... I'm a resident.
You're my boss.

00:54.045 --> 00:55.101
You broke the rules.

00:55.126 --> 00:57.626
[Both laugh]

00:57.789 --> 00:59.056
You want to break some more rules...

00:59.081 --> 01:01.048
in the shower?

01:01.073 --> 01:02.272
- Okay.
- Yeah?

01:02.297 --> 01:03.547
Yeah.

01:03.671 --> 01:05.138
[Cellphone buzzes]

01:05.376 --> 01:07.187
Ugh...

01:07.212 --> 01:08.611
Mmm. I got it.

01:08.636 --> 01:10.547
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

01:10.618 --> 01:12.392
Um... you go ahead.

01:12.417 --> 01:13.562
- I got to take this.
- Okay.

01:13.587 --> 01:14.922
Okay.

01:14.947 --> 01:16.213
[Beeps]

01:16.404 --> 01:19.038
Hey, where are you?

01:19.082 --> 01:21.883
Hey, I'm on a layover in JFK.

01:21.956 --> 01:23.703
Uh, what about you?

01:24.102 --> 01:25.617
Um...

01:25.880 --> 01:28.609
You know, I had a couple days off,

01:28.634 --> 01:30.234
spent them in bed.

01:30.259 --> 01:31.992
<i>Oh, you coming down with something?</i>

01:32.017 --> 01:33.719
I hope not.

01:35.248 --> 01:37.681
So, JFK?

01:37.706 --> 01:38.805
Are you coming home?

01:38.940 --> 01:41.171
Yeah. I had to. [Chuckles]

01:41.196 --> 01:42.851
Toph made me executive of his estate.

01:42.876 --> 01:44.410
[Chuckles] The bastard.

01:44.828 --> 01:46.524
<i>They're closing doors on my flight,</i>

01:46.549 --> 01:47.828
<i>so I'll see you soon.</i>

01:47.853 --> 01:49.468
Have a safe flight.

01:49.493 --> 01:50.492
Bye.

01:50.550 --> 01:51.682
[Shower running]

01:51.707 --> 01:53.041
[Beeps]

01:53.562 --> 01:55.741
♪♪

01:55.766 --> 01:58.035
Drew: Good. Good.

01:58.242 --> 01:59.674
Yep.

02:02.212 --> 02:04.513
Mac: Hey, hey! Looking good, Kenny!

02:04.549 --> 02:06.452
Ahh-ahh! Ready for my smoker, baby!

02:06.477 --> 02:08.009
Take it easy, McGregor, all right.

02:08.044 --> 02:09.531
A little different when
they start hitting back.

02:09.556 --> 02:11.163
Come on.

02:11.188 --> 02:12.688
- Hey.
- Hey.

02:12.803 --> 02:14.501
Shoes on the mat.

02:14.526 --> 02:15.969
Private Locke?

02:19.783 --> 02:22.078
[Distorted] Private Locke?

02:22.102 --> 02:23.866
[Normal] Private Locke?!

02:23.892 --> 02:25.225
Captain Alister.

02:25.260 --> 02:27.147
Just Drew, all right.

02:27.172 --> 02:29.172
No rank here. Just vets,
brothers in arms.

02:29.197 --> 02:30.439
Except me.

02:30.464 --> 02:32.188
Just a brother. Kenny Fournette.

02:32.213 --> 02:33.219
Locke.

02:33.244 --> 02:35.396
Y'all having a fight night, yeah?

02:35.865 --> 02:37.328
It's just some ground and pound...

02:37.353 --> 02:38.646
beat each other up a little bit?

02:38.671 --> 02:40.966
Yeah, it's a support group. Yeah, okay.

02:40.991 --> 02:42.765
So we will train a
little, talk a little.

02:42.790 --> 02:44.122
Winning is about just letting go

02:44.158 --> 02:46.834
of the stuff we're
carrying around with us.

02:47.244 --> 02:48.833
You ever done MMA?

02:48.858 --> 02:51.213
Yeah, I-I got belts.

02:51.528 --> 02:53.883
Jiu-Jitsu, Krav Maga,

02:53.908 --> 02:56.037
- ranked in Muay Thai.
- Nice.

02:56.062 --> 02:57.695
Uh, what's your belt in Jiu Jitsu?

02:57.720 --> 03:00.049
Should've been brown, but
my instructor was a dick,

03:00.074 --> 03:01.340
so that's what happens.

03:01.365 --> 03:03.399
All right. Enough. Go get changed.

03:03.424 --> 03:05.557
Come on, man. I'll show you your locker.

03:06.099 --> 03:07.855
Support group, man?

03:07.880 --> 03:09.680
Come on. Get out of here.

03:09.806 --> 03:11.622
"Should've been brown."

03:11.647 --> 03:13.146
"The instructor was a dick."

03:13.171 --> 03:14.470
What's his story?

03:14.495 --> 03:16.083
He was Humvee gunner in Fallujah.

03:16.108 --> 03:17.279
IED flipped his rig.

03:17.304 --> 03:19.338
He got sent state side with a TBI.

03:19.363 --> 03:20.537
So I thought this would help him.

03:20.562 --> 03:21.490
Yeah, I hope so.

03:21.515 --> 03:23.280
You know, we'll do
what we can, for sure.

03:23.305 --> 03:25.037
Uh, what about you?

03:25.062 --> 03:26.840
When are you gonna get
your ass out there?

03:26.865 --> 03:28.498
Yeah, chemo kicked me in the nuts.

03:28.533 --> 03:29.380
[Grunts]

03:29.405 --> 03:31.457
But my numbers are coming back up.

03:31.482 --> 03:34.029
And so is my gut...
thanks to you and Jordan.

03:34.054 --> 03:35.560
Oh, yeah. That's our fault.

03:35.585 --> 03:37.996
We're never going to leave you
out on the mountain, Mac, right?

03:38.021 --> 03:39.951
You're family now, so just take a seat,

03:39.976 --> 03:41.396
and we'll see what we
can do for the kid.

03:41.421 --> 03:42.997
I appreciate it.

03:43.408 --> 03:46.842
[Indistinct chatter]

03:46.867 --> 03:48.600
[Engines idling]

03:48.625 --> 03:50.459
Cain: Hey, Drs. Diaz and
Rivera from Memorial.

03:50.490 --> 03:52.443
- Where's triage?
- Parking lot.

03:52.468 --> 03:53.707
My guys are clearing the building.

03:53.732 --> 03:54.935
Okay. Get me the known casualties...

03:54.960 --> 03:56.654
Get down!

03:57.551 --> 03:58.950
Ted: Help me!

03:58.975 --> 04:00.154
Help me!

04:00.179 --> 04:01.607
Help me!

04:01.632 --> 04:03.013
Aaah!

04:04.469 --> 04:06.107
Shannon: It's Ted Rogers.

04:06.132 --> 04:07.919
I know him. He's a firefighter.

04:07.944 --> 04:09.677
He's in our ER all the time.

04:09.702 --> 04:10.866
He's off duty.

04:10.891 --> 04:12.334
Called it in on his way home.

04:12.359 --> 04:14.587
- I didn't know he ran in.
- We need a gurney!

04:14.612 --> 04:17.012
Help him! Please! He saved us!

04:17.036 --> 04:18.740
Oh, my God! It's Ted!

04:18.765 --> 04:20.144
1, 2, 3!

04:20.170 --> 04:22.178
[Coughing]

04:22.203 --> 04:23.534
No, no, please!

04:23.559 --> 04:25.526
- We'll go with him, Sara.
- Somebody please help me!

04:25.561 --> 04:27.357
- Please, please, please, my sister!
- No, no, no, no!

04:27.382 --> 04:28.583
My sister's in there! My little sister!

04:28.608 --> 04:29.224
What room?

04:29.249 --> 04:30.436
Naya! She's... she's...
She's on the...

04:30.461 --> 04:31.991
She's on the second floor,
by the ice machine!

04:32.046 --> 04:34.780
- Please! Please!
- Shannon: Hey! Hey! Cain!

04:34.805 --> 04:36.273
Cain, where are you going?!

04:36.298 --> 04:37.903
[Sirens wailing]

04:38.468 --> 04:39.767
- Cain!
- [Smoke alarms blaring]

04:39.792 --> 04:41.303
Drew: Let's just start
with a simple drill...

04:41.328 --> 04:42.718
the guillotine counter.

04:42.743 --> 04:44.616
Ford, want to come in here?

04:44.641 --> 04:47.441
Hey, we're squaring off. Ford shoots.

04:47.466 --> 04:49.132
Saw that coming a mile away.

04:49.157 --> 04:51.358
Hey, can we let the instructor teach?

04:51.456 --> 04:53.422
All right. You're going to shoot.

04:53.447 --> 04:54.679
Good.

04:55.140 --> 04:57.468
I'm going to lock you in the
guillotine, right here.

04:57.493 --> 04:59.460
Once you take that lead
leg, step it around,

04:59.485 --> 05:01.695
and it turns into an easy double.

05:01.720 --> 05:03.551
Enough MMA for dummies. Can we roll?

05:03.576 --> 05:04.741
Hey?

05:05.321 --> 05:07.521
So, if we don't have any more questions,

05:07.546 --> 05:11.047
let's break on 3... 1, 2, 3, break!

05:11.072 --> 05:13.887
Uh... Kenny and Locke, why
don't you guys pair up?

05:14.838 --> 05:16.382
He's got a mouth on him.

05:16.407 --> 05:17.773
He's a YouTube warrior.

05:17.798 --> 05:19.366
This'll humble him.

05:19.722 --> 05:21.973
♪♪

05:27.779 --> 05:29.616
Just a drill.

05:30.378 --> 05:32.478
♪♪

05:37.337 --> 05:38.819
Locke!

05:39.053 --> 05:40.937
[Sound distorts]

05:40.962 --> 05:42.429
[Distantly] Let go.

05:42.454 --> 05:44.217
Locke, let go. He's tapping.
He's tapping!

05:44.242 --> 05:45.421
Locke!

05:45.446 --> 05:48.576
Locke, Locke!

05:51.421 --> 05:54.355
[Sound returns]

05:54.380 --> 05:56.279
Dude, what the hell?!

05:56.304 --> 05:57.929
Locke?! Hey?!

05:57.954 --> 05:59.014
Kenny, you okay?

05:59.039 --> 06:00.592
Yeah, I just...

06:00.617 --> 06:02.030
[Groans]

06:02.055 --> 06:03.867
Don't move.

06:03.891 --> 06:05.773
- What?
- I...

06:05.798 --> 06:07.101
I can't feel my feet.

06:07.126 --> 06:08.825
Ford, call an ambulance!

06:08.850 --> 06:11.421
- Drew, I can't feel my feet.
- Go! Call an ambulance!

06:11.446 --> 06:13.366
Now!

06:13.710 --> 06:16.116
Hey, hey, hey. It's going to be okay.

06:16.208 --> 06:19.366
I didn't know what to do! Naya...
She's stuck in there!

06:19.391 --> 06:21.458
Calm down. Just calm down, okay?

06:21.483 --> 06:23.216
[Alarm beeping]

06:24.877 --> 06:26.910
Naya?!

06:26.935 --> 06:28.405
Naya?!

06:28.901 --> 06:30.634
[Coughs]

06:30.659 --> 06:31.825
Can you hear me?!

06:31.850 --> 06:33.477
Naya?!

06:33.502 --> 06:35.068
Naya?!

06:35.093 --> 06:36.874
[Coughs]

06:37.397 --> 06:38.897
Naya?!

06:38.922 --> 06:41.530
[Alarm continues]

06:42.079 --> 06:43.946
Where are you?!

06:44.847 --> 06:46.448
[Grunts]

06:48.472 --> 06:50.599
I've got you. I've got you.

06:50.624 --> 06:53.330
[Coughs]

06:53.618 --> 06:55.616
It's okay. I got you.

06:55.641 --> 06:57.132
♪♪

06:57.157 --> 06:58.554
We're gonna get out of here.

06:58.579 --> 07:01.234
[Grunts, coughs]

07:01.259 --> 07:03.210
♪♪

