07:18.948 --> 07:21.783
- Oh, my God, it's Naya!
- Stop, stop!

07:21.830 --> 07:23.290
She's in altered!

07:23.315 --> 07:24.743
I'll find a vein! Get the Narcan!

07:24.768 --> 07:26.018
An OD? Are you sure?

07:26.043 --> 07:27.697
Yeah, check the pupils.

07:29.855 --> 07:32.385
They're pinpoint. How old is she?

07:32.410 --> 07:33.576
She'll be 13 in November.

07:33.674 --> 07:34.946
She's got a lot of problems, okay?

07:34.971 --> 07:36.622
It's a long story. Would
you just help her?

07:36.647 --> 07:37.932
[Gasps]

07:37.957 --> 07:38.956
Naya!

07:38.981 --> 07:40.948
Get off me! No! No! Get off me!

07:40.973 --> 07:42.002
[Screams]

07:42.027 --> 07:43.329
Naya?! Naya?! Naya?!

07:43.353 --> 07:44.626
- No! Get off me!
- Naya, it's okay.

07:44.652 --> 07:45.551
- No!
- Naya?! Naya?!

07:45.576 --> 07:47.260
- No! No!
- Naya! It's okay!

07:47.285 --> 07:48.855
- It's Izzy! It's Izzy!
- No!

07:48.880 --> 07:51.237
Stop. Listen. You're fine. You're okay.

07:51.262 --> 07:52.534
I know, I know, I know.

07:52.559 --> 07:54.797
Shh. You're fine, you're okay.
You're good.

07:54.822 --> 07:56.424
Let's go. Get her in the ambulance.

07:56.449 --> 07:58.116
You, too, Izzy.

07:58.141 --> 07:59.974
♪♪

07:59.999 --> 08:01.580
It's just withdrawal agitation.

08:01.605 --> 08:02.533
I know. I'm good.

08:02.558 --> 08:03.857
All right, let's go.

08:03.882 --> 08:05.736
Paul says you're a urologist at Penn.

08:05.761 --> 08:09.196
Yeah, I know it's an
unusual field for a woman.

08:09.221 --> 08:12.040
I picked it to keep my
dad out of my business.

08:12.065 --> 08:13.658
Dads don't like to talk about penises

08:13.683 --> 08:14.596
with their little girl.

08:14.621 --> 08:15.520
Yeah, nor does your brother.

08:15.545 --> 08:16.721
Well, we're glad you're here.

08:16.746 --> 08:18.315
And I know Julian wanted
you to take a look

08:18.340 --> 08:19.472
at the VA expansion plans.

08:19.497 --> 08:21.283
First, I want to meet
this purple-haired woman

08:21.308 --> 08:24.033
who has her claws so
deep into my baby bro.

08:24.058 --> 08:26.363
Okay, wow, You just mentioned
that in front of my <i> two</i> bosses.

08:26.388 --> 08:28.939
Uh... anyways, Jordan, do
you know where Shannon is?

08:28.964 --> 08:30.604
Yeah, she's doing a
hotel fire with Cain.

08:30.629 --> 08:32.020
They're doing mass cas triage on site.

08:32.046 --> 08:33.073
Sometime later then, I guess.

08:33.099 --> 08:34.052
Great.

08:34.077 --> 08:37.903
Jordan, it's Ted Rogers.
He's having a STEMI.

08:37.928 --> 08:38.966
How bad?

08:38.991 --> 08:41.365
He's awake and talking now.
0-2 sat is 95%.

08:41.390 --> 08:43.068
Hey, Ted, it's Jordan.

08:43.092 --> 08:44.529
When did the chest pain start?

08:44.554 --> 08:45.770
Ted: In the ambulance.

08:45.795 --> 08:46.994
- Feels tight.
- Scott: Yeah.

08:47.019 --> 08:48.848
You're having a heart
attack, but we got you.

08:48.873 --> 08:52.108
Send a stat gas in a co-ox
for a carbon monoxide level.

08:52.133 --> 08:53.318
All right. Let's go.

08:53.343 --> 08:54.904
Okay, everybody, on three.

08:54.929 --> 08:56.539
1, 2, 3!

08:56.564 --> 08:58.955
[Grunts]

08:58.980 --> 09:00.802
Ted, do you have any cardiac history?

09:00.827 --> 09:02.686
No, the job keeps me in shape.

09:02.711 --> 09:04.478
Julie and I ran the half-marathon

09:04.503 --> 09:06.131
last year after the baby came.

09:06.156 --> 09:08.086
I was on a diaper run.

09:08.111 --> 09:10.092
I saw the flames, went to help.

09:10.117 --> 09:11.936
I got some maids out.

09:11.961 --> 09:13.326
Wish I did more.

09:13.351 --> 09:15.484
You did plenty. That
took a lot of balls.

09:15.509 --> 09:16.674
Anything else bothering you?

09:16.699 --> 09:17.898
[Strained] My abdomen.

09:17.923 --> 09:19.222
But my chest...[grunts]

09:19.247 --> 09:20.474
Jocelyn: CO level is 13.

09:20.499 --> 09:21.818
All right. We got you now, Ted.

09:21.843 --> 09:23.349
We're going to take care of your
heart attack right here, okay?

09:23.375 --> 09:24.273
Mollie: Jordan?

09:24.298 --> 09:26.350
Kenny's coming in as a patient.

09:26.375 --> 09:28.155
- What?
- Jordan, go.

09:28.180 --> 09:29.927
Be with Kenny. I got Ted.

09:29.952 --> 09:31.779
♪♪

09:31.804 --> 09:33.536
Drew: Jordan?!

09:33.561 --> 09:35.807
Kenny, it's going to be okay.
You hear me?

09:35.832 --> 09:37.498
He's got a c-spine
hyperextension injury.

09:37.523 --> 09:38.655
- It's T10 level.
- All right.

09:38.680 --> 09:39.631
Let's get him to Trauma 2.

09:39.656 --> 09:41.489
Yo! It was an accident!

09:41.787 --> 09:44.077
Oh, this is Locke... blunt-head trauma,

09:44.102 --> 09:45.756
brief L.O.C, vitals are stable.

09:45.781 --> 09:47.209
Hot doc. Me likey.

09:47.234 --> 09:48.267
Hey, watch your mouth, Locke!

09:48.292 --> 09:49.959
- How'd this happen?
- Ask Drew.

09:49.984 --> 09:51.435
Hey, he's fine, all right?

09:51.460 --> 09:52.755
Medics did it by the
book with the c-collar.

09:52.780 --> 09:53.746
I'm going to see Kenny.

09:53.771 --> 09:56.096
All right, let's get him to Exam 1.

09:56.279 --> 09:57.745
What the hell happened?

09:57.770 --> 09:59.646
Locke's the vet I told you needed help.

09:59.671 --> 10:02.238
He made a mistake with Kenny.
He held on too long.

10:02.317 --> 10:04.771
You know, stuff happens. It's not chess.

10:04.796 --> 10:06.898
Then Drew goes all Jon Jones on him.

10:06.923 --> 10:08.192
I'm assuming that's a bad thing.

10:08.217 --> 10:10.250
Yeah, real bad... total overreaction.

10:10.275 --> 10:11.841
- Okay. You all right?
- Yeah.

10:11.866 --> 10:14.240
Okay, I'm gonna take care of Kenny.

10:19.164 --> 10:21.467
Scott, is... is it my C2?
You can tell me, man.

10:21.492 --> 10:22.992
Hey, when we know, you know.

10:23.027 --> 10:24.031
Let's tart with some X-rays.

10:24.056 --> 10:25.622
You can get some steroids on board.

10:25.647 --> 10:26.985
All right, Kenny.

10:27.010 --> 10:29.591
I want you to tell me when you
can feel any of this, okay?

10:29.616 --> 10:31.299
[Weakly] Okay.

10:31.324 --> 10:33.414
♪♪

10:35.225 --> 10:36.991
Is he doing it?

10:37.103 --> 10:38.420
Drew?

10:38.445 --> 10:40.764
Just, uh... Just tell
him when you feel it.

10:40.791 --> 10:42.179
Oh, God.

10:42.204 --> 10:43.552
Keep going.

10:43.577 --> 10:45.109
Take it easy.

10:45.568 --> 10:48.816
[Whimpers]

10:49.695 --> 10:51.511
Scott: How about this?

10:51.536 --> 10:53.278
No.

10:58.094 --> 11:00.108
I feel that! I feel that.

11:00.144 --> 11:03.344
Okay, so it's up to my T4 now.

11:03.369 --> 11:05.548
Oh, God, I can't believe
this is happening.

11:05.573 --> 11:07.138
Okay, his bladder's distended.

11:07.163 --> 11:08.733
He's needs a Foley. Mollie?

11:08.758 --> 11:11.234
What, a catheter?! No.
Not from Mollie, no.

11:11.259 --> 11:13.204
You know you can't pee
with this kind of injury.

11:13.229 --> 11:14.422
Look, I don't care.

11:14.447 --> 11:17.140
Look, I don't want anyone
I know draining my junk.

11:17.165 --> 11:18.750
Okay, I got to work here.

11:19.267 --> 11:20.399
Actually, you know what?

11:20.434 --> 11:22.702
There's probably someone
here who can help us out.

11:22.737 --> 11:23.984
I'll be right back.

11:24.009 --> 11:25.977
Mollie, come with me.

11:27.434 --> 11:29.233
Okay, honey, I know you're scared.

11:29.258 --> 11:31.254
But we are going to give you
everything that we have.

11:31.279 --> 11:32.430
You know that.

11:32.875 --> 11:34.908
- Y... Yeah.
- Okay.

11:34.933 --> 11:36.750
Jordan, there's a problem with Ted.

11:36.775 --> 11:37.978
Paul needs you.

11:38.226 --> 11:39.628
- Go.
- Yeah?

11:39.653 --> 11:41.094
I got him.

11:41.185 --> 11:42.469
- [Monitor beeping rapidly]
- What happened?

11:42.494 --> 11:43.721
Acute abdomen out of nowhere.

11:43.746 --> 11:45.167
Cain and Shannon have a
code-Y from the fire.

11:45.192 --> 11:46.491
EKG came back normal.

11:46.526 --> 11:47.866
Started complaining of
pain and dizziness.

11:47.891 --> 11:49.457
All right, he needs an
airway, a stat chest X-ray,

11:49.492 --> 11:50.257
and a bedside ultrasound.

11:50.292 --> 11:51.836
I'll be right back.

11:52.266 --> 11:54.761
Cain: Opiate OD. She's apneic again.

11:54.786 --> 11:56.008
Gave her two doses of Narcan in the rig.

11:56.033 --> 11:57.842
Okay. Trauma 3 for intubation.

11:57.867 --> 11:59.406
Narcan? She's a kid.

11:59.431 --> 12:00.710
Shannon: 13 in November.

12:00.735 --> 12:02.280
Classic case of upper-middle class

12:02.305 --> 12:04.266
absentee parenting, if you ask me.

12:04.291 --> 12:04.969
I didn't.

12:04.994 --> 12:06.057
Jocelyn: I couldn't get a BP.

12:06.082 --> 12:07.814
- Pulse is in the 200s.
- Cain: She's in torsades.

12:07.839 --> 12:10.141
1, 2, 3! Go!

12:10.166 --> 12:11.711
Shannon, I want you to
start compressions.

12:11.736 --> 12:13.102
Cain, defibrillation.

12:13.127 --> 12:14.750
And, Jocelyn, push magnesium.

12:14.775 --> 12:16.072
Oh, my God. Is she gonna die?

12:16.097 --> 12:17.262
Naya's very sick.

12:17.287 --> 12:18.754
We need your mom's consent to treat her.

12:18.779 --> 12:20.562
You need to reach her now! Go!

12:20.587 --> 12:23.368
♪♪

12:29.898 --> 12:31.991
Prior to our arrival on the scene,

12:32.016 --> 12:33.897
it was one of our own, Ted Rogers,

12:33.922 --> 12:36.781
<i>who entered the building and
proceeded to evacuate...</i>

12:37.057 --> 12:38.579
Hey, doc?

12:38.604 --> 12:41.512
How much longer? I'm
growing roots over here.

12:41.634 --> 12:44.297
CT's backed up and you still
need to get your lac repaired.

12:44.322 --> 12:46.255
Hey, how's Kenny?

12:46.280 --> 12:48.086
Well, we've given him steroids

12:48.111 --> 12:49.609
to reduce the swelling in his spine,

12:49.634 --> 12:51.743
so, at the moment, it's
just hurry up and wait.

12:51.768 --> 12:53.243
Yeah, Locke, you haven't signed

12:53.268 --> 12:54.567
your consent-to-treatment form.

12:54.592 --> 12:56.372
I don't need a machine to
tell me I got my bell rung.

12:56.397 --> 12:58.000
That's exactly what you
need, chuckle-head.

12:58.025 --> 12:59.235
If she says do it, you're doing it.

12:59.260 --> 13:00.530
Cain?

13:00.555 --> 13:01.621
Hey.

13:01.675 --> 13:03.055
How's your OD doing?

13:03.080 --> 13:04.539
Not good... still no mom.

13:04.564 --> 13:05.547
The sister says she's on the way,

13:05.572 --> 13:07.313
which is, apparently, not
fast enough for Shannon.

13:07.338 --> 13:09.070
All right, look, uh... these cases,

13:09.095 --> 13:10.469
they sort of hit close
to home to Shannon.

13:10.494 --> 13:11.032
Mm-hmm

13:11.057 --> 13:13.500
So she might be a little
bit mouthier than usual.

13:13.525 --> 13:16.273
Just do me a favor, keep
an eye on her, okay?

13:16.298 --> 13:18.065
I got to go. That's Ted's wife.

13:18.090 --> 13:19.089
Julie?

13:19.114 --> 13:20.613
Hi. I'm Dr. Alexander.

13:20.638 --> 13:21.930
I was here the night that you delivered?

13:21.955 --> 13:23.720
I remember.

13:23.745 --> 13:25.222
How's he doing?

13:25.247 --> 13:27.875
Well, he suffered a heart attack

13:27.900 --> 13:30.906
and has possible carbon
monoxide poisoning.

13:30.931 --> 13:33.813
<i>But</i> he's stable, okay?

13:34.854 --> 13:36.469
Is he going to make it?

13:36.810 --> 13:38.610
You and I both know how strong Ted is.

13:38.635 --> 13:39.834
[Chuckles] Yeah.

13:39.859 --> 13:41.219
He's such a good dad.

13:41.244 --> 13:42.776
Yeah.

13:42.801 --> 13:45.039
I didn't even know we
ran out of diapers.

13:45.064 --> 13:46.230
♪♪

13:46.255 --> 13:48.781
She's still burning up,
hanging antibiotics now.

13:48.806 --> 13:50.306
I found the source of infection.

13:50.331 --> 13:51.601
She has a septic knee.

13:51.626 --> 13:52.758
Yeah, that's a possibility.

13:52.783 --> 13:55.210
Come... Come listen to her chest.

13:59.453 --> 14:01.353
She has a heart murmur.

14:01.378 --> 14:03.676
So, you're thinking endocarditis?

14:03.701 --> 14:05.667
I'll page Dr. Clemmens for you.

14:05.801 --> 14:07.844
What's wrong, Shannon?

14:08.390 --> 14:10.750
Her heart may have an infection.

14:10.775 --> 14:12.391
She may need an operation to fix it.

14:12.416 --> 14:14.157
We need your mom's consent.
Where is she?

14:14.182 --> 14:16.172
On her way. She was working.

14:16.197 --> 14:17.657
Her boss wouldn't approve a transfer

14:17.682 --> 14:19.116
until she finished her project.

14:19.141 --> 14:20.580
She can give consent over the phone.

14:20.605 --> 14:21.555
I'll give her a call.

14:21.580 --> 14:22.969
I'll... I'll call her.

14:22.994 --> 14:25.079
Her... Her boss can be a real dick.

14:25.104 --> 14:27.743
But I'll bring in the phone
as soon as she answers.

14:34.594 --> 14:36.127
Doesn't that seem weird to you?

14:36.162 --> 14:37.928
Mom hasn't called in yet or anything?

14:37.964 --> 14:39.629
She just said her mom was at work.

14:39.664 --> 14:41.569
You wouldn't drop everything
as soon as you find out

14:41.594 --> 14:42.626
your kid's in the ER?

14:42.662 --> 14:43.976
Okay, listen.

14:44.001 --> 14:45.934
Less conspiracy, more work.

14:45.959 --> 14:47.526
Get Scott in here, have him do an ECHO.

14:47.551 --> 14:50.055
I've got to see another patient.

14:50.204 --> 14:51.938
[Sighs]

15:03.274 --> 15:05.368
- Jocelyn?
- Yes, doctor?

15:05.393 --> 15:06.715
Run this down to the lab for me.

15:06.740 --> 15:08.050
I need a gram stain stat.

15:08.075 --> 15:09.241
Yes, doctor.

15:11.465 --> 15:14.032
Bud, I'm so sorry. I... I didn't...

15:14.057 --> 15:16.025
It's not your fault.

15:16.391 --> 15:18.028
[Sighs] I...

15:18.053 --> 15:20.028
He was talking trash. I should've known.

15:20.052 --> 15:21.618
I should've rolled with him myself.

15:21.643 --> 15:23.962
Hello? Someone needs a catheter?

15:23.987 --> 15:25.486
Uh... Kenny here.

15:25.511 --> 15:27.117
Hi, Kenny.

15:27.142 --> 15:29.262
I'm Dr. Bella Cummings.

15:30.098 --> 15:32.648
Bella, as in "Paul's sister, Bella"?

15:32.673 --> 15:34.309
That's me.

15:35.368 --> 15:38.603
I'm sorry we couldn't meet
under better circumstances.

15:38.962 --> 15:40.412
Could you step out, please?

15:40.437 --> 15:41.681
Give the man some privacy?

15:41.706 --> 15:43.735
All right.

15:44.507 --> 15:47.173
All right, Kenny, just
take a few deep breaths.

15:47.198 --> 15:50.532
- I'll have this donein no time.
- [Door closes]

15:50.557 --> 15:54.150
So, I understand you work in the ER.

15:54.175 --> 15:55.469
My home away from home.

15:55.494 --> 15:56.593
Hmm.

15:58.142 --> 16:00.026
And I'm spending so much
time taking care of people,

16:00.051 --> 16:02.032
you never think you'd end up lying here.

16:02.057 --> 16:06.797
Well, you have a lot of
people who care about you...

16:07.468 --> 16:09.201
like my brother Paul.

16:09.226 --> 16:10.805
Well, he cares about you, too.

16:10.830 --> 16:11.696
[Chuckles] Mm.

16:11.721 --> 16:14.689
That's all we've been hearing...
Bella, Bella, Bella.

16:14.714 --> 16:16.329
You... You know what? Um...

16:16.354 --> 16:17.453
Yo, could you just give me a minute

16:17.478 --> 16:18.841
just to, you know,

16:18.866 --> 16:21.733
just mentally prepare for this...
this intrusion?

16:21.758 --> 16:22.790
No.

16:22.815 --> 16:23.983
No?

16:24.157 --> 16:26.306
But... You've got to be kidding me.

16:26.331 --> 16:28.154
I'm already done.

16:28.179 --> 16:29.321
What?

16:29.346 --> 16:30.922
That... That's it?

16:30.947 --> 16:33.376
I told you I was good.

16:33.591 --> 16:35.453
Look...

16:35.478 --> 16:38.478
I know this is really, really tough.

16:38.996 --> 16:41.664
But everything Paul tells me about you

16:41.689 --> 16:43.805
tells <i> me</i> that you will handle this

16:43.830 --> 16:45.730
with strength and dignity.

16:46.883 --> 16:48.275
Dr. Cummings?

16:48.300 --> 16:49.827
They're asking for you in Trauma 1.

16:49.852 --> 16:51.352
All right, Kenny, just relax.

16:51.377 --> 16:53.221
I'll get your doc back in here.

16:58.309 --> 16:59.619
[Sighs]

16:59.644 --> 17:01.143
♪♪

17:01.178 --> 17:03.245
Paul: BP is 70/38.

17:03.281 --> 17:05.847
Hang two units of O-neg and
then send a STAT hemoglobin.

17:05.872 --> 17:07.400
Yeah, he's not getting enough oxygen.

17:07.424 --> 17:08.530
You have to take him to surgery.

17:08.555 --> 17:09.414
How can I help?

17:09.440 --> 17:10.372
Positive FAST.

17:10.396 --> 17:11.462
We missed it because of a heart attack.

17:11.487 --> 17:13.765
May I? Yeah, but I need
to get him up to the OR

17:13.790 --> 17:14.867
for an ex-lap to stop the bleeding.

17:14.893 --> 17:16.633
- No, you don't.
- That's not blood in his abdomen.

17:16.656 --> 17:17.462
It's urine.

17:17.487 --> 17:18.836
No way that's just a perforated bladder.

17:18.861 --> 17:20.795
Think about it, Paul. Hemoglobin is 12.

17:20.829 --> 17:23.188
He became unstable after
all of the IV fluids.

17:23.213 --> 17:25.079
Well, there's only one
way to find out. A DPL?

17:25.105 --> 17:27.339
You need to relieve the pressure in
his abdomen so that he can breathe,

17:27.364 --> 17:29.280
then you and Bella can repair
his bladder in the OR.

17:29.305 --> 17:30.634
That's if you're willing to do it.

17:30.659 --> 17:31.735
Of course, I just need surgical...

17:31.760 --> 17:33.856
- Privileges, yes.
- Scott's already granted them.

17:33.881 --> 17:36.009
- Okay.
- Doctor?

17:36.034 --> 17:37.867
Placing the DPL.

17:39.955 --> 17:41.921
Careful.

17:41.946 --> 17:44.907
♪♪

17:46.156 --> 17:47.729
Nice work, bro.

17:47.754 --> 17:50.153
Now let's get him to the OR.

17:50.790 --> 17:52.667
She's a damn pecker checker.

17:52.692 --> 17:55.192
Yeah, now we know why Paul
always calls her a surgeon.

17:55.227 --> 17:56.826
[Knock on door]

17:56.851 --> 17:58.745
Hey.

17:59.082 --> 18:01.648
He's cool.

18:01.997 --> 18:03.708
How's my brawler?

18:08.860 --> 18:10.985
[Chuckling] Sausage fest in here.

18:11.010 --> 18:12.218
You're the reason he's in here.

18:12.243 --> 18:14.277
He knows. He's here to pay his respects.

18:14.302 --> 18:15.311
Locke?

18:18.114 --> 18:19.980
I'm sorry, man.

18:22.217 --> 18:23.962
I, um...

18:24.961 --> 18:26.290
Hey, look at this.

18:26.315 --> 18:27.700
I got my bell rung, too.

18:27.725 --> 18:29.962
Five stitches 'cause doc
here cheap-shotted me.

18:29.987 --> 18:31.005
I cheap-shotted you?!

18:31.030 --> 18:32.396
Hey, let it go.

18:32.421 --> 18:33.641
He's here to apologize to Kenny.

18:33.666 --> 18:35.699
Then tell him to apologize and get out.

18:35.724 --> 18:37.241
It's cool.

18:37.488 --> 18:40.212
This could just as easily have been you.

18:40.600 --> 18:43.998
I doubt that, but I hope...
I hope you get better.

18:46.126 --> 18:48.507
Hey, guys. Can I get a minute?

18:48.532 --> 18:50.593
Sure. I got to get Locke to a CT.

18:50.618 --> 18:51.587
Hang in there, Kenny.

18:51.612 --> 18:52.778
Thanks, Mac.

18:52.803 --> 18:54.516
Good news.

18:54.819 --> 18:57.275
No fractures or
dislocations on the X-rays.

18:57.300 --> 18:59.025
[Clatters]

18:59.050 --> 19:00.890
They're gonna dock your pay for that.
[Chuckles]

19:00.915 --> 19:02.415
It didn't slip, I couldn't hold it.

19:02.440 --> 19:04.525
My... My arms are getting weak.

19:04.550 --> 19:07.274
Hey, raise your... raise
your arms up for me.

19:07.299 --> 19:09.532
Squeeze my fingers.

19:09.689 --> 19:11.488
Squeeze 'em.

19:11.513 --> 19:12.720
Scott, it's getting worse!

19:12.745 --> 19:13.891
Scott?!

19:13.916 --> 19:15.407
It's getting w... What's happening?!

19:15.432 --> 19:17.725
Hey, the steroids are going
to kick in in a bit.

19:17.750 --> 19:19.837
Next step is, we're gonna
go get you an MRI.

19:19.862 --> 19:21.915
For... For spinal cord damage?!

19:21.940 --> 19:24.203
I... I hurt my back playing ball, yo!

19:24.228 --> 19:25.275
I can't be paralyzed!

19:25.300 --> 19:26.432
[Sobbing]

19:26.457 --> 19:28.664
- I can't be paralyzed!
- It's okay, Kenny.

19:28.689 --> 19:31.165
Just give the steroids
some time to kick in.

19:31.190 --> 19:32.989
[Indistinct talking]

19:33.435 --> 19:36.134
♪♪

19:42.570 --> 19:43.835
Let's go, folks!

19:43.860 --> 19:46.272
Get those crowbars out and
open up your wallets.

19:46.297 --> 19:48.000
This is for Ted and his family.

19:48.025 --> 19:50.172
And I want to see
Jacksons, not Lincolns.

19:50.197 --> 19:51.360
[ <i> Indistinct talking over P.A.</i> ]

19:51.385 --> 19:52.550
Hey.

19:52.624 --> 19:54.429
Chest X-ray shows a pulmonary edema.

19:54.454 --> 19:55.461
What are those?

19:55.486 --> 19:57.152
Staghorn kidney stones on a 12 year old,

19:57.177 --> 19:57.937
that's a little weird.

19:57.962 --> 19:59.262
Yeah, so's this.

19:59.287 --> 20:01.704
Endocarditis with severe
aortic regurgitation.

20:01.729 --> 20:03.368
One of the worst cases I've ever seen.

20:03.393 --> 20:05.984
Shannon, here are the
labs you asked for.

20:06.009 --> 20:08.438
I ran a gram stain on
the pus in her knee.

20:08.463 --> 20:10.796
It's positive for Neisseria gonorrhea.

20:10.821 --> 20:13.189
That would explain the size of
the vegetation in her heart.

20:13.214 --> 20:14.697
We got to get her up to the OR.

20:14.722 --> 20:16.188
- Where's the mom?
- She's not here yet.

20:16.213 --> 20:18.122
- [Machine beeping rapidly]
- She's in shock,

20:18.147 --> 20:19.680
and she's got a ring
abscess in her heart.

20:19.705 --> 20:21.338
If I don't operate now, she's gonna die.

20:21.363 --> 20:22.862
- Ready?
- Ready.

20:22.887 --> 20:24.196
Let's go.

20:25.292 --> 20:27.509
You tapped her knee without telling me?

20:27.534 --> 20:29.534
And I might've saved her life, too.

20:29.569 --> 20:32.314
No, and I'm glad, but you need
to tell me what you're doing.

20:32.354 --> 20:33.775
<i>You're</i> not my boss, Cain.

20:33.800 --> 20:34.784
Last time I checked,

20:34.809 --> 20:36.135
you're technically a
first-year resident.

20:36.160 --> 20:37.612
Who's forgotten more
than you'll ever know.

20:37.637 --> 20:39.170
- Show some respect.
- Says the man who told me,

20:39.205 --> 20:41.339
"Less conspiracy, more work."

20:41.374 --> 20:43.979
I tried telling you I had
a feeling about this.

20:44.004 --> 20:45.354
You totally dismissed me.

20:45.379 --> 20:46.670
Because of your background, I...

20:46.695 --> 20:47.894
What do you know about my background?

20:47.919 --> 20:49.585
[Sighs]

20:49.654 --> 20:51.161
Jordan told you to watch me?

20:51.186 --> 20:52.114
No.

20:52.139 --> 20:54.239
Save it. You're a lousy liar.

20:58.229 --> 21:00.478
- Hey! Clear! Clear, clear.
- How we doing?

21:00.503 --> 21:03.392
Foley's in, vitals stable,
but paralysis is ascending.

21:03.417 --> 21:04.464
We need to intubate him.

21:04.489 --> 21:06.878
I may be paralyzed, but my
ears still work, Jordan.

21:06.903 --> 21:09.117
Kenny, if your quadriplegia
gets any worse,

21:09.142 --> 21:11.276
your diaphragm will become immobilized.

21:11.301 --> 21:13.620
If you get into that MRI
and you can't breathe,

21:13.645 --> 21:14.753
you are not going to be able to tell us.

21:14.778 --> 21:16.177
- I refuse intubation.
- Kenny...

21:16.202 --> 21:18.160
Look, I don't have a
DNR or a living will

21:18.185 --> 21:19.798
or even an organ donor card!

21:19.823 --> 21:21.065
Okay, who's gonna make decisions for me

21:21.090 --> 21:22.362
- if I don't wake up?!
- I'll call your mom in Shreveport.

21:22.387 --> 21:23.416
No, she's been a mess
since my gramm passed!

21:23.441 --> 21:25.276
Kenny, we will be right there.

21:25.301 --> 21:27.058
Look, Jordan, I have to be able to talk!

21:27.083 --> 21:29.214
Okay?! I'm all I got!

21:29.238 --> 21:31.106
So no damn tube, are we clear?!

21:31.131 --> 21:32.597
Yeah, we're clear...

21:32.622 --> 21:36.044
[Breathing heavily]

21:36.854 --> 21:38.120
All right.

21:38.145 --> 21:40.335
1, 2, 3!

21:40.360 --> 21:43.394
[Monitor beeping steadily]

21:43.419 --> 21:45.276
[Water running]

21:45.301 --> 21:47.448
First time in the OR together, baby bro.

21:47.473 --> 21:48.557
You excited?

21:48.582 --> 21:49.614
Nope.

21:49.639 --> 21:51.479
Remember when we used
to operate on my dolls

21:51.504 --> 21:52.799
when we were little?

21:52.825 --> 21:56.198
Uh... I-I recall you
decapitating my GI Joes.

21:56.223 --> 21:57.361
Research.

21:57.386 --> 21:58.886
Oh, yeah.

21:59.929 --> 22:01.195
Hey.

22:01.220 --> 22:03.534
Hi. Shannon. You must be Bella.

22:03.559 --> 22:05.826
I need a quick curbside. Oh, hey.

22:05.861 --> 22:07.720
Oh, we're actually... Ted
has a ruptured bladder,

22:07.745 --> 22:08.811
so we're headed to the OR right now.

22:08.846 --> 22:10.178
You're a urologist, right?

22:10.214 --> 22:11.206
My patient has...

22:11.231 --> 22:12.612
Staghorn calculi.

22:12.637 --> 22:14.627
She also has disseminated gonorrhea.

22:14.652 --> 22:16.229
Is your patient a prostitute?

22:16.480 --> 22:17.946
♪♪

22:17.971 --> 22:19.416
Cain: How's Naya?

22:19.441 --> 22:20.588
Scott: Not great.

22:20.613 --> 22:23.514
A piece of vegetation
embolized to her left leg.

22:23.539 --> 22:24.737
So, we'll have Paul come in

22:24.762 --> 22:26.216
and do an angio and a thrombectomy.

22:26.241 --> 22:28.575
Paul's next door in
surgery on the fireman.

22:28.650 --> 22:31.217
I got to fix her heart
before I can fix her leg.

22:31.242 --> 22:33.436
I'm worried she could lose it.

22:33.710 --> 22:36.424
♪♪

22:36.449 --> 22:38.315
You want to walk me through it?

22:38.887 --> 22:40.653
You ever done one?

22:40.678 --> 22:43.104
I ran an ER in Nogales for eight years.

22:43.129 --> 22:45.239
I did whatever needed to be done.

22:45.372 --> 22:47.739
Scrub in. You're hired.

22:50.236 --> 22:51.602
[Water running]

22:51.627 --> 22:53.312
So, I hear you're from Dallas.

22:53.337 --> 22:54.169
Yeah.

22:54.194 --> 22:55.841
I was a nurse at Memorial.

22:55.866 --> 22:57.891
I trained there. It's a great hospital.

22:57.916 --> 22:59.315
Yeah.

22:59.340 --> 23:01.422
So, how are you liking things here?

23:01.650 --> 23:03.215
Actually, I'm loving it.

23:03.329 --> 23:05.509
Yeah, that's what I hear.

23:06.697 --> 23:08.413
Meaning what exactly?

23:08.438 --> 23:10.571
Nothing exactly.

23:10.656 --> 23:12.355
Listen, I don't know
what you're implying,

23:12.380 --> 23:14.514
but if you have something
to say, say it.

23:14.943 --> 23:19.016
I know you ran an ER in Mexico,
but you're a <i> resident</i> here.

23:19.041 --> 23:21.883
And if H.R. finds out about
you and Jordan, your boss,

23:21.908 --> 23:23.273
they could can her.

23:23.298 --> 23:25.071
I don't want to see that happen.

23:25.445 --> 23:27.111
I don't know what you're talking about.

23:27.217 --> 23:28.344
Good.

23:28.369 --> 23:29.950
Then she's safe.

23:30.756 --> 23:34.234
All right, partner. Get
ready to place that line.

23:36.269 --> 23:39.235
Just give it time for the
steroids to kick in, okay?

23:39.260 --> 23:40.961
I'll be right in there.

23:43.955 --> 23:46.717
[Breathing heavily]

23:49.277 --> 23:51.719
[MRI whirring, clanking]

23:51.744 --> 23:54.392
I need your help, Gramm.

23:56.848 --> 23:59.105
It's messed up.

23:59.423 --> 24:01.122
The wrong guy's in that tube.

24:01.147 --> 24:02.719
Don't go there, Drew.

24:02.744 --> 24:04.443
It doesn't do any good.

24:10.761 --> 24:12.494
Hey, is that Locke's VA file?

24:12.530 --> 24:13.695
Yeah. He's our patient.

24:13.731 --> 24:15.073
No, he's <i> my</i> patient.

24:15.098 --> 24:16.417
Yeah, well, take a look at
your patient's history.

24:16.442 --> 24:17.191
- No, Drew...
- Hey!

24:17.216 --> 24:18.546
You cannot look at that!

24:18.571 --> 24:20.472
"Multiple psychiatric hospitalizations!"

24:20.497 --> 24:21.929
Take a look.

24:21.954 --> 24:23.715
He came to my class off his meds,

24:23.740 --> 24:24.972
and now Kenny might be in a wheelchair

24:25.008 --> 24:26.273
for the rest of his life.

24:26.770 --> 24:28.355
Where are you going?

24:28.380 --> 24:30.589
I'm going to tell Mac. He
needs to know about this.

24:30.614 --> 24:32.747
[Door opens, closes]

24:33.048 --> 24:36.067
♪♪

24:40.652 --> 24:42.753
[Sirens wailing in distance]

24:42.778 --> 24:44.371
Hey!

24:44.396 --> 24:45.995
Locke was hospitalized!

24:46.213 --> 24:48.013
- Refused his meds!
- I'm not gonna read that.

24:48.038 --> 24:49.738
You had no right digging
up his VA records.

24:49.785 --> 24:51.139
He's unstable, Mac!

24:51.164 --> 24:52.230
What don't you understand about that?

24:52.265 --> 24:53.164
He's a little off.

24:53.199 --> 24:54.433
No, he's more than a little off.

24:54.458 --> 24:55.657
- Keep reading.
- I'm not gonna.

24:55.682 --> 24:56.915
Then I'll fill you in.

24:56.940 --> 24:59.415
Locke was never blown
up in a Humvee in Iraq.

24:59.644 --> 25:01.728
The Army kicked him out first.

25:01.896 --> 25:03.529
They wouldn't even send him over there!

25:03.554 --> 25:04.863
Do you know how crazy you have to be

25:04.888 --> 25:06.386
to get kicked out of the
Army during a war?!

25:06.411 --> 25:07.522
So what now, Drew...

25:07.547 --> 25:08.441
you just gonna kick him to the curb?

25:08.466 --> 25:09.899
No, he needs a psych evaluation.

25:09.924 --> 25:10.972
Oh, great. More doctors.

25:10.997 --> 25:12.521
Hey, my best friend might be paralyzed

25:12.546 --> 25:13.778
because of this guy!

25:13.803 --> 25:15.636
So I'm sorry if I'm not
sympathetic enough for you!

25:15.661 --> 25:17.652
It's not about me, Drew!
It's about Locke.

25:17.773 --> 25:20.034
And it's not his fault
that some sleazy recruiter

25:20.059 --> 25:21.367
pushed him through to make his quota.

25:21.392 --> 25:23.960
But he served in the Army.
He's one of us.

25:23.995 --> 25:25.294
He's not... No, no! He's not.

25:25.329 --> 25:26.529
Don't even come at me
with that right now.

25:26.565 --> 25:27.897
He's one of the brotherhood,

25:27.933 --> 25:29.198
all right, and right now,

25:29.230 --> 25:31.261
I'm waiting on CT scans
from you knocking him out

25:31.286 --> 25:32.472
to make sure nothing
else is wrong with him.

25:32.497 --> 25:33.918
Oh, please! I got someone
who's like a brother

25:33.943 --> 25:35.313
lying in a tube right now,

25:35.338 --> 25:36.672
hoping he's going to
be able to walk again,

25:36.707 --> 25:37.886
because of this son of a bitch!

25:37.911 --> 25:38.941
That's great, Drew.

25:38.966 --> 25:41.916
Wipe your ass with
your Hippocratic oath.

25:42.399 --> 25:43.956
What'd you just say to me?

25:43.981 --> 25:46.712
Big-time doctor... forgot
where you came from.

25:46.762 --> 25:48.160
You can go to hell!

25:48.185 --> 25:50.230
I already been there, pal.

25:52.526 --> 25:54.079
Mollie: Hey, sweetheart.

25:54.104 --> 25:56.034
I'm taking up a collection
for Ted and his family.

25:56.059 --> 25:57.758
You got a little something
you'd like to give?

25:57.794 --> 25:59.126
Yeah, sure.

25:59.161 --> 26:01.028
♪♪

26:01.064 --> 26:02.930
Paul: Ted survived a
heart attack and burns

26:02.955 --> 26:04.098
and a ruptured bladder. [Crying]

26:04.133 --> 26:05.566
He is a tough S.O.B.

26:05.602 --> 26:07.501
Clearly, he wanted to
live for his family.

26:07.536 --> 26:09.862
[Crying] Oh, thank you, Dr. Cummings.

26:10.113 --> 26:12.355
Both Dr. Cummings, I guess.

26:12.380 --> 26:14.948
Hey, hey, we're just
doing our job, okay?

26:14.973 --> 26:17.245
- Ted did the hard part.
- It's okay, baby girl.

26:17.280 --> 26:20.052
Daddy's okay. Daddy's okay.

26:20.311 --> 26:22.714
♪♪

26:24.097 --> 26:25.580
How's Naya?

26:25.794 --> 26:27.920
She's still in surgery.

26:29.175 --> 26:32.987
It's been four hours, Izzy.
Your mom's not coming.

26:35.590 --> 26:38.191
She's not your real mom, is she?

26:38.299 --> 26:40.391
She your foster mom?

26:41.417 --> 26:43.727
Reece is better than my mom.

26:44.760 --> 26:47.232
You need to tell me what's going on.

26:47.424 --> 26:49.457
Where are you really from?

26:54.641 --> 26:56.610
Cincinnati.

26:57.831 --> 26:59.712
My dad...

26:59.856 --> 27:02.163
OD'd when I was 14.

27:04.131 --> 27:06.571
And my mom was a tweaker.

27:06.934 --> 27:10.836
So I just got on a bus to Miami,

27:11.036 --> 27:14.070
and when I ran out of money,
I started sleeping on...

27:14.184 --> 27:17.493
on beaches, and that's
where Reece found me.

27:18.123 --> 27:21.724
And she bought me clothes and food.

27:22.215 --> 27:24.669
And... And we... we travel all over.

27:24.694 --> 27:26.735
We'd go to Super Bowls and stuff.

27:26.986 --> 27:30.816
I know that that feels
like she cares about you.

27:31.682 --> 27:34.987
But she's pimping you and
Naya out, isn't she?

27:37.535 --> 27:39.282
She's using you.

27:39.307 --> 27:40.993
I'm not gonna snitch.

27:41.018 --> 27:43.118
She doesn't care about you, Izzy.

27:43.209 --> 27:44.969
That's why she's not here.

27:44.994 --> 27:46.794
She knows that if she showed her face,

27:46.819 --> 27:48.375
she would go to jail.

27:48.665 --> 27:51.712
And what about the men
that come around, huh?

27:53.637 --> 27:55.466
Why don't they pay?

28:01.096 --> 28:03.296
Who are you talking about Izzy?

28:03.885 --> 28:06.186
♪♪

28:09.401 --> 28:11.078
[Breathing heavily]

28:11.103 --> 28:11.968
Kenny?

28:11.993 --> 28:13.259
Tell me how you're feeling.

28:13.284 --> 28:15.418
Jordan... Jordan, I can feel my feet!

28:15.443 --> 28:17.010
Yeah? That's good.

28:17.035 --> 28:18.467
- [Laughs]
- That's really good.

28:18.492 --> 28:20.432
Here, honey. Can you squeeze my hands?

28:20.457 --> 28:22.131
- [Both laugh]
- Yeah.

28:22.156 --> 28:23.389
That's really good.

28:23.424 --> 28:24.703
- All right.
- Help me up.

28:24.728 --> 28:26.227
- Yeah?
- Help me up.

28:26.252 --> 28:27.406
Hey.

28:27.431 --> 28:29.063
[Groans]

28:29.359 --> 28:31.325
Steroids are kicking in.

28:31.867 --> 28:34.421
I was in there thinking about my gramm.

28:34.567 --> 28:36.199
She always used to say,

28:36.224 --> 28:38.258
"Live every day like it's your last."

28:39.140 --> 28:42.804
Seems like a bumper sticker
until this happens.

28:42.878 --> 28:44.978
So, what are you going to do today?

28:45.003 --> 28:46.195
[Laughs]

28:46.227 --> 28:48.069
Well, first thing on the agenda

28:48.094 --> 28:49.359
is getting this catheter removed.

28:49.384 --> 28:50.316
Mmm.

28:50.341 --> 28:51.774
You want me to page Dr. Bella?

28:51.799 --> 28:53.336
- Oh, God, no.
- [Laughs]

28:53.361 --> 28:54.427
I'll find me a temp.

28:54.452 --> 28:55.656
All right.

28:55.681 --> 28:57.212
I'm also going to have to
find you a room, all right?

28:57.237 --> 28:59.054
We need to monitor you
for another night.

28:59.079 --> 29:00.679
Thank you.

29:00.704 --> 29:01.960
All right, I'll be right back.

29:01.985 --> 29:03.151
All right.

29:03.176 --> 29:04.842
♪♪

29:04.867 --> 29:06.054
[Door opens, closes]

29:06.079 --> 29:07.788
Thanks, Gramm.

29:09.660 --> 29:11.827
So the good news is, he's stable.

29:11.852 --> 29:13.156
And with your support,

29:13.181 --> 29:16.039
Ted will be off helping people
before you know it, okay?

29:16.064 --> 29:18.030
[Pager beeping]

29:18.055 --> 29:19.179
Thank you.

29:19.204 --> 29:21.648
[Indistinct chatter]

29:22.016 --> 29:25.451
<i>Dr. Alexander, code white. Dr.
Alexander, code white.</i>

29:25.476 --> 29:27.610
- Shannon, is she crashing?!
- Shannon: No.

29:27.635 --> 29:29.109
But you called a code white.

29:29.134 --> 29:31.625
I needed to show you something.

29:31.650 --> 29:35.774
Naya and Izzy were trafficked
by a woman named Reece Oskin.

29:36.061 --> 29:38.089
She abandoned them after the fire.

29:39.127 --> 29:40.894
Okay, Shannon, did you call the police?

29:40.919 --> 29:42.752
Yeah.

29:42.777 --> 29:44.342
That's how we got this tape.

29:44.469 --> 29:45.902
It's hotel security,

29:45.927 --> 29:48.495
about an hour before the fire.

29:53.563 --> 29:58.104
Izzy: Reece took advantage of
me when I ran away from home.

29:58.322 --> 30:01.078
And then she got me to buddy up to Naya

30:01.103 --> 30:04.136
and convince her to join our family.

30:09.641 --> 30:13.645
She said I was too old for
some of our regular clients...

30:14.491 --> 30:16.187
like Ted.

30:16.397 --> 30:18.734
♪♪

30:26.678 --> 30:29.237
He wasn't on a diaper run, Jordan.

30:29.542 --> 30:33.411
♪♪

30:35.722 --> 30:36.988
[Sighs]

30:37.013 --> 30:38.479
[Coughs]

30:41.222 --> 30:42.799
[Inhales deeply]

30:47.431 --> 30:49.031
Jordan.

30:49.933 --> 30:52.167
You saved me. I really owe you.

30:52.192 --> 30:54.394
It's not me you owe.

30:55.221 --> 30:56.768
What are you saying?

30:56.793 --> 30:57.961
You're being arrested

30:57.986 --> 30:59.918
for having sex with a trafficked minor.

30:59.943 --> 31:01.527
Wh... What?

31:02.314 --> 31:03.947
Jordan. You know me.

31:03.972 --> 31:06.767
No, I thought I did, but
I really I had no idea

31:06.792 --> 31:08.098
who you are until now.

31:08.123 --> 31:10.286
- You can't be serious.
- Don't do it, Ted.

31:10.311 --> 31:12.503
- You're going to believe them.
- Don't you dare.

31:12.535 --> 31:15.736
Do not play the hero versus a
couple of junkie runaways.

31:15.761 --> 31:18.893
We have video of you going
into her hotel room.

31:19.087 --> 31:22.003
We're doing a rape exam on Naya
that will confirm your DNA.

31:22.028 --> 31:23.969
- Hey, Jordan...
- She's 12 years old, Ted.

31:24.002 --> 31:25.748
- Don't...
- And you left her to burn

31:25.773 --> 31:27.719
so you could cover up what you did.

31:29.536 --> 31:31.056
You have a daughter.

31:31.081 --> 31:32.280
Jordan, I am begging you...

31:32.305 --> 31:34.476
Ted. You're okay.

31:34.616 --> 31:36.789
[Voice breaking] You're okay, honey.

31:36.814 --> 31:38.194
Hi, sweetie.

31:38.219 --> 31:39.423
No! No, no, no.

31:39.448 --> 31:40.597
Julie, give me your daughter.

31:40.622 --> 31:41.864
- What is going on?
- Give her to me.

31:41.889 --> 31:43.206
- Jordan...
- Don't!

31:43.231 --> 31:45.331
You explain it to her, because I can't.

31:45.356 --> 31:46.555
I'm sorry, Julie.

31:46.668 --> 31:48.409
♪♪

31:48.434 --> 31:50.366
[Crying]

31:50.896 --> 31:53.198
♪♪

31:56.609 --> 31:59.292
♪♪

32:06.881 --> 32:10.944
- ♪ Come rest your weary head ♪
- Dad?

32:11.363 --> 32:16.756
♪ It's hard giving life to dead ♪

32:17.259 --> 32:20.393
- ♪ Some things can't be unsaid ♪
- You remembered her family.

32:20.418 --> 32:23.453
- ♪ But I'll try ♪
- We met in Seattle

32:23.568 --> 32:26.919
- ♪ But I'll try ♪
- at this big video game conference.

32:26.944 --> 32:28.951
♪ Remember when we were young ♪

32:28.976 --> 32:31.817
Her family's been looking
for her for two years.

32:32.085 --> 32:37.265
♪ And the summer was never done ♪

32:37.865 --> 32:39.599
Unlike yours.

32:39.624 --> 32:42.935
♪ When did winter block out our sun ♪

32:42.960 --> 32:45.594
- ♪ From our sky ♪
- I've been with Reece for four years.

32:45.630 --> 32:48.231
♪ From our sky ♪

32:48.266 --> 32:50.479
I... I don't know where to go.

32:50.504 --> 32:53.635
♪ Don't give up hope 'cause
the river still flows ♪

32:53.670 --> 32:56.505
- ♪ And I'm coming home ♪
- You're 18, Izzy.

32:56.540 --> 32:59.241
- ♪ And I'm coming home ♪
- You can do whatever you want to do.

32:59.276 --> 33:01.343
- ♪ It's not over yet ♪
- Yeah.

33:01.378 --> 33:04.179
♪ Hearts still beating in our chest ♪

33:04.206 --> 33:08.474
♪ So don't let go ♪

33:08.518 --> 33:11.986
- ♪ 'Cause I'm coming home ♪
- My first foster was a smoker.

33:12.011 --> 33:14.211
He always said I was his ashtray.

33:14.236 --> 33:16.457
♪ I'm coming home ♪

33:16.492 --> 33:18.792
This was from a belt buckle.

33:18.827 --> 33:20.961
She said it was for my own good.

33:20.996 --> 33:24.017
♪♪

33:24.042 --> 33:26.309
I got past my scars.

33:26.334 --> 33:28.001
So can you.

33:34.886 --> 33:37.833
I thought that was for the fireman.

33:38.146 --> 33:40.895
I decided you and Naya
could use it more.

33:41.882 --> 33:44.270
- ♪ I've got a cannonball ♪
- It'll fly her home

33:44.294 --> 33:45.903
- and help me get you
- ♪ So let's watch ♪

33:45.928 --> 33:47.918
- an apartment and a job.
- ♪ all the boulders fall ♪

33:47.944 --> 33:49.001
We'll also get you some counseling

33:49.037 --> 33:51.067
if... that's what you want.

33:51.092 --> 33:52.505
I...

33:52.530 --> 33:54.536
♪ 'Cause there is no one after all ♪

33:54.561 --> 33:56.272
[Scoffs] I don't know what to say.

33:56.297 --> 33:58.114
♪ Just our lies ♪

33:58.139 --> 33:59.052
♪ Just our lies ♪

33:59.077 --> 34:01.765
You didn't... you didn't
have to do any of this.

34:01.801 --> 34:04.208
♪ Don't give up hope 'cause
the river still flows ♪

34:04.233 --> 34:06.723
It's about time somebody
was on your side.

34:06.762 --> 34:08.239
♪ And I'm coming home ♪

34:08.264 --> 34:10.918
You've had a crappy
first 18 years, Izzy.

34:10.944 --> 34:12.464
♪ And I'm coming home ♪

34:12.489 --> 34:13.935
- I know it's going to be hard
- ♪ It's not over yet, ♪

34:13.960 --> 34:15.512
- to ever trust anyone again,
- ♪ heart's still beating chest ♪

34:15.547 --> 34:19.446
- but... this is a first step.
- ♪ So don't let go ♪

34:20.170 --> 34:22.646
And maybe someday, you'll
find another family,

34:22.670 --> 34:24.670
just like I did.

34:26.599 --> 34:28.599
[Chuckles]

34:28.985 --> 34:32.007
♪♪

34:33.032 --> 34:35.931
♪ Ooh ♪

34:35.956 --> 34:38.030
♪ Ooh-ooh ooh ♪

34:38.054 --> 34:41.074
Twice as many camera crews
for the pedophile fireman

34:41.100 --> 34:42.873
than there was for the hotel hero.

34:43.085 --> 34:44.507
What's with that?

34:44.725 --> 34:48.154
You know, people not being
who we think they are.

34:48.179 --> 34:49.844
We fall for it every time.

34:49.891 --> 34:51.248
Yeah.

34:51.426 --> 34:53.625
[Cellphone buzzing]

34:54.067 --> 34:55.616
I got to take this.

34:55.641 --> 34:57.429
Yeah.

34:58.687 --> 35:00.020
Hey, Kenny.

35:00.045 --> 35:02.045
Sorry... Sorry I wasn't able to
make it down to see you, man.

35:02.070 --> 35:03.237
Aww, that's okay, man.

35:03.262 --> 35:05.095
You had your hands full with Ted.

35:05.261 --> 35:07.827
Scott said the MRI
showed mild cord edema,

35:07.852 --> 35:09.194
but the swelling should go down.

35:09.219 --> 35:11.286
I'll, uh... I'll be back to normal soon.

35:11.340 --> 35:13.631
Hey, you... You met Bella? Right?

35:13.736 --> 35:15.913
That's an introduction
I'll never forget.

35:15.938 --> 35:17.704
[Chuckles] Me, neither.

35:17.729 --> 35:18.895
[Chuckles]

35:18.920 --> 35:19.943
Okay.

35:19.968 --> 35:21.842
Um... So, we should get going.

35:21.867 --> 35:23.772
All right, I hired a car to
take us around San Antonio,

35:23.797 --> 35:25.498
- see the spots.
- Right.

35:25.523 --> 35:26.957
Uh... rain check.

35:26.982 --> 35:28.115
I have plans.

35:28.140 --> 35:30.241
Uh... maybe tomorrow?

35:30.266 --> 35:31.699
Plans? With whom?

35:31.724 --> 35:33.920
Hmm. Wouldn't you like to know?

35:34.014 --> 35:36.009
Yes, that's why I asked.

35:36.190 --> 35:38.490
So, Shannon,

35:38.622 --> 35:40.654
Paul said you were afraid to meet me?

35:40.806 --> 35:42.976
I'm not that bad, am I?

35:43.038 --> 35:44.805
No, you're great.

35:44.830 --> 35:46.460
I was just nervous.

35:46.485 --> 35:48.652
I'm a judger that doesn't
like to be judged.

35:48.677 --> 35:50.780
And Paul asked me not
to pull my usual crap

35:50.805 --> 35:52.225
in front of his sister.

35:52.372 --> 35:55.242
He said you could be kind
of uptight, like your dad.

35:55.266 --> 35:56.545
He was worried you weren't
going to like me,

35:56.570 --> 35:57.538
because I'm a smartass.

35:57.563 --> 36:00.030
I'm not as uptight as
he thinks, you know?

36:00.055 --> 36:02.494
Especially after a few Bloody Marys.

36:02.519 --> 36:03.819
Drink?

36:03.844 --> 36:06.178
What about Paul? Won't
that piss him off?

36:06.238 --> 36:08.560
And teach him to stop trying to control

36:08.585 --> 36:10.788
the most important women in his life.

36:10.813 --> 36:12.577
Okay. You're on.

36:12.602 --> 36:13.734
[Chuckles]

36:13.759 --> 36:16.038
[Indistinct chatter]

36:16.643 --> 36:18.584
Thanks for coming.

36:18.609 --> 36:20.976
I didn't drag you away
from anything, did I?

36:21.001 --> 36:23.201
Nothing more important than this.

36:27.403 --> 36:29.302
Topher's Barracuda.

36:32.481 --> 36:36.171
He drove it to the airport,
so it's been here since...

36:38.624 --> 36:41.258
Janet wanted me to have it.

36:41.293 --> 36:43.335
♪♪

36:43.479 --> 36:44.833
There's a zillion cars out here.

36:44.858 --> 36:46.075
Does he have, like, an emergency button

36:46.100 --> 36:48.100
- or something?
- No. It's old school.

36:48.125 --> 36:49.457
Right.

36:51.581 --> 36:53.335
So...

36:53.752 --> 36:55.213
How are you?

36:57.453 --> 36:59.086
Okay.

36:59.233 --> 37:00.456
Okay?

37:00.481 --> 37:01.613
Yeah.

37:01.638 --> 37:04.287
Syd told Drew that you
were captured by rebels

37:04.312 --> 37:05.999
and you got shot.

37:06.024 --> 37:07.990
Yeah, it was, uh...

37:08.015 --> 37:09.644
interesting.

37:10.295 --> 37:12.647
I'm going to go back in a month to help.

37:13.041 --> 37:14.573
[Chuckles]

37:14.598 --> 37:16.398
What's her name?

37:16.491 --> 37:18.615
[Both laugh]

37:21.157 --> 37:23.323
Hard to miss, huh?

37:30.512 --> 37:33.877
You know, I've been
avoiding coming back here.

37:34.580 --> 37:36.160
'Cause once I did, it'll...

37:36.185 --> 37:38.855
- Make it all real.
- Yeah.

37:40.138 --> 37:42.305
I've lost two brothers now.

37:42.330 --> 37:44.160
No.

37:44.382 --> 37:47.216
Tee, as long as you and I are here...

37:47.241 --> 37:48.659
Topher's not gone.

37:48.684 --> 37:49.941
The three amigos.

37:49.966 --> 37:51.686
Yes.

37:56.416 --> 37:58.050
[Lock disengages]

37:58.075 --> 37:59.742
[Car door opens]

38:00.373 --> 38:01.872
[Clears throat]

38:07.715 --> 38:08.880
[Car door closes]

38:24.328 --> 38:26.028
Want to get out of here?

38:26.063 --> 38:27.530
Yeah, I do.

38:27.565 --> 38:29.531
♪♪

38:29.566 --> 38:32.549
[Engine starts]

38:32.574 --> 38:34.458
<i>♪ We can dance if we want to ♪</i>

38:34.483 --> 38:36.841
- <i>♪ We can leave your friends behind ♪</i>
- [Both laugh]

38:36.866 --> 38:39.003
<i>♪ 'Cause your friends don't
dance and if they don't dance ♪</i>

38:39.028 --> 38:40.345
You gotta be kidding me.

38:40.370 --> 38:41.378
- <i>♪ Well, they're no friends ♪</i>
- No, man. Topher used

38:41.403 --> 38:42.861
- <i>♪ of mine ♪</i>
- to love this song.

38:42.902 --> 38:44.495
<i>♪ I say, we can go where we want to ♪</i>

38:44.520 --> 38:46.182
<i>♪ There's a place they will never find ♪</i>

38:46.207 --> 38:46.995
He's still here, T.C.

38:47.020 --> 38:48.800
<i>♪ And we can act like we
come Rom out of this world ♪</i>

38:48.825 --> 38:50.315
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

38:50.340 --> 38:51.446
<i>♪ Leave the real one far behind ♪</i>

38:51.471 --> 38:53.284
Okay.

38:53.778 --> 38:56.412
♪♪

39:01.384 --> 39:03.951
♪ Ooh, it's the safety dance ♪

39:03.976 --> 39:05.751
♪ Ooh, it's the safety dance ♪

39:05.776 --> 39:07.237
- Mac? Mac?
- No.

39:07.262 --> 39:08.994
I was out of line earlier.

39:09.994 --> 39:12.100
I was out of line. I'm sorry.

39:12.677 --> 39:14.299
All right.

39:14.454 --> 39:15.820
Forget it.

39:15.845 --> 39:17.978
I don't blame you.

39:18.003 --> 39:19.702
[Sighs] So, where's Locke?

39:19.727 --> 39:21.191
Is he still in CT?

39:21.216 --> 39:22.736
Never made it.

39:22.761 --> 39:24.182
He took off before.

39:24.207 --> 39:25.705
We got into it a bit.

39:25.730 --> 39:26.962
About what?

39:26.991 --> 39:30.502
I told him we'd have
to cool it on the MMA.

39:30.527 --> 39:32.394
[Sighs]

39:32.728 --> 39:35.758
All right, look, if you...
if you think it'll help him,

39:35.783 --> 39:37.369
just bring him by again, all right?

39:37.394 --> 39:40.202
I'll give him a private lesson.
I'll roll with him.

39:40.227 --> 39:42.230
I just didn't think, you know...

39:42.255 --> 39:45.181
I mean, Kenny was still too new,
so I shouldn't have done it.

39:45.206 --> 39:47.373
Yeah, I figured you might say that.

39:47.398 --> 39:49.164
I called him. I told him to come back.

39:49.189 --> 39:51.624
You're a good man, Mac.

39:51.657 --> 39:54.822
Not much to look at, but good man.

39:54.896 --> 39:57.129
Just paying it forward, bro.

39:57.836 --> 40:00.150
Look, I was a lot like Locke.

40:00.175 --> 40:01.994
I had that tumor in my
head the size of a lemon,

40:02.019 --> 40:03.785
made me squirrelly.

40:03.810 --> 40:05.120
You guys didn't give up on me,

40:05.145 --> 40:07.212
gave me my life back.

40:07.237 --> 40:08.756
I figured, I brought Locke around,

40:08.781 --> 40:09.914
you could do the same.

40:09.939 --> 40:11.783
We'll take another crack at it.

40:11.808 --> 40:13.587
In the meantime, how
'bout something to eat?

40:13.612 --> 40:15.126
Uh... Oz's?

40:15.151 --> 40:16.962
- I'm buying.
- Pbht!

40:16.987 --> 40:18.421
Hope you brought your credit card, man.

40:18.446 --> 40:19.929
I can chow when someone else is buying.

40:19.954 --> 40:20.720
All right, well, see you there.

40:20.745 --> 40:21.911
- Yeah.
- All right.

40:31.246 --> 40:32.915
Hey, buddy.

40:35.286 --> 40:37.227
Where you been?

40:40.369 --> 40:42.524
Man, you...

40:43.194 --> 40:44.859
Oh, man.

40:48.778 --> 40:50.478
You lied to me.

40:50.622 --> 40:52.429
No, Locke. Hold... Hold on, listen.

40:52.454 --> 40:54.035
You tricked me, man.

40:54.183 --> 40:57.484
You're my best friend...

40:57.652 --> 41:00.120
and you lied to me.

41:00.225 --> 41:01.670
Locke, come on. Look at me.

41:01.695 --> 41:02.973
All right, listen. All right?

41:02.998 --> 41:03.931
Hey, look at me.

41:03.956 --> 41:05.449
[Grunts]

41:05.474 --> 41:06.747
[Metal clatters]

41:06.772 --> 41:09.106
Damn it! Damn it!

41:09.130 --> 41:10.649
- Drew!
- Mac?!

41:10.681 --> 41:12.677
- Drew, help!
- Mac! Mac! Mac!

41:12.702 --> 41:15.228
No, no, no, no, no! No, no!
No, no, no, no, no, no!

41:15.253 --> 41:16.744
Mac, no! Mac!

41:16.769 --> 41:18.681
♪ I saw the sun ♪

41:18.706 --> 41:21.125
- ♪ Start to fade ♪
- Mollie! Jocelyn, get a gurney!

41:21.150 --> 41:23.696
[Groaning]

41:23.721 --> 41:25.291
- Stay... stay with me, right here.
- [Breathing shakily]

41:25.316 --> 41:27.478
- [Strained] Let me go.
- ♪ As the days ♪

41:27.503 --> 41:30.471
- ♪ Slip away ♪
- Let me go.

